T1  - Marketmaker Behavior in an Auction Market: An Analysis of Scalpers in Futures Markets
AU  - SILBER, WILLIAM L.
Y1  - 1984/09/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1984.tb03886.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 937
EP  - 953
VL  - 39
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1984.tb03886.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT This paper focuses on the role of scalpers as marketmakers in the competitive auction of futures exchanges. We use transactions data of a representative scalper to identify the source of scalper earnings. We find that scalpers provide liquidity services to incoming market orders, thereby facilitating commercial hedging. Scalper earnings are positively related to the bid-asked spread and negatively related to the length of time a position is held.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Futures Markets and Informational Efficiency: A Laboratory Examination
AU  - FORSYTHE, ROBERT
AU  - PALFREY, THOMAS R.
AU  - PLOTT, CHARLES R.
Y1  - 1984/09/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1984.tb03887.x
T2  - The Journal of Finance
JF  - The Journal of Finance
JO  - The Journal of Finance
JA  - The Journal of Finance
SP  - 955
EP  - 981
VL  - 39
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0022-1082
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1984.tb03887.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT Through the use of laboratory market methodology, the effect of a futures market on the time path of asset prices is studied and competing models of asset pricing are analyzed. With replication of market conditions, the predictions of a rational expectations equilibrium model are relatively accurate whether or not futures markets are present. However, the presence of futures markets increases the speed with which an efficient equilibrium is achieved. While this more rapid adjustment can increase the variance of spot market prices as they move to equilibrium, this increased variance reflects efficiency gains due to better information.
ER  - 

