Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ABSTRACT In this paper, we show that taxes motivate the flow of trade credit without involving the assumption of credit market imperfections. The direction of trade credit flow depends on the distribution of marginal tax rates among buyers and sellers. In equilibrium, the trade credit decision follows a tax-induced clientele on both the supply and demand side.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Effects of Inflation and Money Supply Announcements on Interest Rates
AU  - URICH, THOMAS
AU  - WACHTEL, PAUL
Y1  - 1984/09/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1540-6261.1984.tb03901.x
